Burgmoser Munchen", has an ornate silver "AB" inlaid on bow of trigger guard, has "Original Syst Aydt 7924" stamped on one side of the breech block and a "B" with a small proof type mark on the other side of the breech block.  The number may actually read 7024 instead of 7924.  The stocks appear to be a very fine walnut, with some curl present in the buttstock but a fairly plain forearm held by a single wedge.  There is a deep cheek cup in the buttstock and a thumb rest on the opposite side.  Right hand shooter.  The wrist is checkered.  The rifle has a fine removable double set trigger.  There is a very nice fixed post rear sight with windage and elevation, and a globe type front sight with insert.  A front sling swivel stud is located on the barrel, but is missing on the buttstock although the hole where it was loccated is present.  The barrel is 31 1/2" long, fluted forward of the forearm, and appears to be 8.15X46 Caliber.  This is a good midrange target round.  It is easily made using 30-30 Winchester brass.  Dies are available.
